54.6	Challah	Challah	Challah (Hebrew: חלה) also khale (eastern Yiddish), (German and western Yiddish), berches (Swabian), barkis (Gothenburg), bergis (Stockholm), birkata in Judeo-Amharic, chałka (Polish), colaci (Romanian), vánočka (Czech), Zopf (Switzerland) and kitke (South Africa), is a special braided bread eaten on the Sabbath and holidays.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/09/Challah_Bread_Six_Braid_1.JPG/275px-Challah_Bread_Six_Braid_1.JPG
